[4] Ebola as a bioterror threat: discounted
Date: Tue 21 Oct 2014
Source: Daily Mail [edited]
http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2802599/ebola-infected-suicide-bombers-moment-controversial-senator-jacqui-lambie-got-shut-senior-defence-chiefs-asking-silly-question.html


Are we [Australia] at risk from Ebola-infected suicide bombers?
---------------------------------------------------------------
Senator Lambie [former soldier] asks defence chiefs if the nation [Australia] is at risk from Ebola infected 'suicide agents'. Defence chiefs say there is no evidence Australia is at risk from hypothetical militants. It comes as she called for 'M.A.S.H.-style' mobile military hospitals to fight the deadly virus here and abroad last week.... -- more

[byline: Daniel Piotrowski]

[Since the question of whether Ebola is an actual bioterror threat has been asked by some media (more than once), has anybody done the following experiment? Infected a 60 kg pig, fitted it with human clothing and a suicide vest, blown it up inside a bomb control tent containing a few pigskin-covered mannequins wearing human clothes (in a BL-4 chamber, of course) and after the explosion swabbed the mannequins exposed pigskin, their clothing, any bits and pieces and the inside of the tent, and tested them for RNA and live virus? Then we would have some evidence of whether the virus is incinerated by the explosion and the potential risk, rather than just speculation. (If a test has already been done, the results are probably classified). And of course, even if it is shown to be effective at contaminating surviving bystanders and their rescuers, it doesn't mean that it will ever happen. - Mod.JW]

